  ```

Additional Preferences:
- Try to include toy DataFrame creation code once and share it for later theory/problem blocks (if reasonable)
- Do not let practice problems copy the theory section material: they must challenge the same 
knowledge, but look different
- Make problems concrete with specified expected outputs
- Have more frequent practice sections (after each concept)
- Use real-world-like column names (like grade_math_midterm instead of just column1)
- For complex concepts like regex, provide more elaborate examples
- Keep your answers very minimalistic: I am working fast and I don't want to spend time reading your reasoning

